ass=title>   ...</span><hr size=1> &quot;I hope I'm still on track here. Let me know if I'm wrong about something so far.&quot;<br>
<br>
You are on track so far. In fact, everything you said is true except the fact that block being greater then parry is not where the problem lies. It's that monks are on a whole nother evasive TABLE. AC has 2 parts, mitigation and avoidance. Monks are on their own avoidance table, always have been. This is why they are getting nerfed instead of warriors/sks/pallies getting buffed. They already have a huge advantage over every tanking class. Then you toss in Combat Agility (even more evasion) Combat Stability (even more mitigation) and ND (even more hitpoints) and it doesn't matter how much better the warrior is then the monk because the monk is MORE then good enough to beat the mob.<br>
<br>
Does that make more sense? Stop looking at it in terms of warrior V monk and look at it in terms of Monk V MOB. Just cause a warrior can get 7500 hps doesn't mean a monk with 5500 isn't the better tank. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaragirlancot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aragir Lancot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/15/02 8:22:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1386.topic&index=122>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Aha!  different avoidance tables.  I gotcha.<br>
